cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as aspect and opinion term extraction from product reviews. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method to automatically mine extraction rules and train a neural model for the task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses training procedures for the neural model. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as aspect and opinion term extraction can be seen as a subtask of information retrieval. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes an algorithm for rule mining.
